      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric E or ASME V&V 20 area metric) applied to hemolysis index predictions vs. experimental data across all 5 operating points, with statistical significance testing at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error is reported but no formal validation metric per ASME V&V 20 is applied. Statistical significance testing is absent. Predictions agree within 30% at 3 of 5 operating points — insufficient for Gradation 4. Achieved level 2."
